        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 1:44PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 144 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mc Coy, or near Newport, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Blacksburg...
Christiansburg...
Radford...
Dublin...
Pembroke...
Mountain Lake...
and Newport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
